  "question": "This demand curve shows that...",
  "options": [
   "as consumers get better off, they buy more",
   "if consumers buy more, the price will rise",
   "if the price falls, consumers buy more",
   "if the price rises, producers will sell more"
  ],
  "caseStudy": "<img src=\"/images/economics/2-2-demand-curve-q2-extracted.png\" alt=\"A demand curve from the OCR exam paper: Price on the vertical axis, Quantity on the horizontal axis, with a straight line labelled D sloping downwards from left to right\" style=\"display:block;width:100%;max-width:420px;margin:14px auto;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;background:#fff;padding:6px;\" />",
  "hint": "The curve links the good's own PRICE to QUANTITY demanded — nothing else. Which option only talks about those two things, in the right direction?",
