  "question": "The diagram shows the market supply and demand curves for a good. If there is a decrease in supply, how will this affect the equilibrium price and quantity?",
  "options": [
   "The price will decrease and quantity will increase",
   "The price will increase and quantity will decrease",
   "The quantity will increase but price will not change",
   "There will be no change because the market is in equilibrium"
  ],
  "caseStudy": "<img src=\"/images/economics/2-4-q20-supply-demand-extracted.png\" alt=\"Diagram from the OCR exam paper showing a market with curves labelled Supply and Demand crossing at price p1 and quantity q1\" style=\"display:block;width:100%;max-width:440px;margin:14px auto;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;background:#fff;padding:6px;\" />",
  "hint": "Whatever the diagram looks like, the chain is fixed: supply DECREASES (shifts left) → price UP, quantity DOWN.",
