   "markScheme": "<div class=\"marks-section\">\n<h5>Mark Scheme — 2 marks (AO1b)</h5>\n<p>The official answer diagram:</p>\n<img src=\"/images/economics/2-4-equilibrium-answer-extracted.png\" alt=\"Official mark scheme diagram: a downward-sloping demand curve D and upward-sloping supply curve S crossing, with dotted lines marking the equilibrium price p and quantity q\" style=\"display:block;width:100%;max-width:420px;margin:10px auto;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;background:#fff;padding:6px;\" />\n<ul>\n<li>Give 2 marks for a clear diagram showing a supply and demand curve with an equilibrium point indicated (in some way) where the two lines cross.</li>\n<li>Give 1 mark for a correct diagram with no equilibrium indicated.</li>\n<li>No reward for a diagram which confuses supply and demand curves OR does not label both of them.</li>\n</ul>\n<h5>Examiner's Comments</h5>\n<p>Most candidates were able to draw a correctly labelled diagram worth two marks. However, marks were lost by candidates who labelled supply and demand incorrectly or who did not show the equilibrium between the two market forces.</p>\n</div>",
